-- AF Gruppen to Build Sewage Treatment Plants in Norway’s Bergen
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-07-04T16:01:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/af-gruppen-to-build-sewage-treatment-plants-in-norway-s-bergen.html
AF Gruppen ASA (AFG) , a Norwegian
construction company, won about 220 million kroner ($37 million)
of contracts to build sewage treatment plants in Bergen. The
Flesland and Holen facilities when completed next year will
handle sewage water for almost 300,000 people, the Oslo-based
company said today on its website.  “Infrastructure projects within fresh water supply and
sewage is a growing market in  Norway ,” AF Group Chief Executive
Officer Pal Egil Ronn said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
